 fight men & mocking Christianity with a drag queen last supper opening ceremony, the Paris Olympics made triathlon competitors swim in the polluted river Seine, causing them to profusely vomit.\", \"from\": 849, \"to\": 1070, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 897, \"end\": 909, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9992587687081919, \"rank\": 0.000721953295602129, \"text\": \"Christianity\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"INSANE.\", \"from\": 1071, \"to\": 1078, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1071, \"end\": 1077, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/INSANE_(software)\", \"score\": 0.9239691088250689, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"INSANE\", \"types\": [\"Q7397\", \"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/INSANE_(software)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/INSANE_(software)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Dad joke intended.\", \"from\": 1079, \"to\": 1097, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1079, \"end\": 1087, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dad_joke\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Dad joke\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dad_joke\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dad_joke\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Report:https://t.co/uHHNL4N8EVpic.twitter.com/sUzmDEPBuh  After complaints, some training sessions in the riverwere cancelled last week.\", \"from\": 1098, \"to\": 1234, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Now,\\u00a0Belgian athlete Claire Michel and two other Swiss athletes have had to forfeit a mixed-team relay race.\", \"from\": 1236, \"to\": 1344, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1241, \"end\": 1248, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\", \"score\": 0.8864394935273845, \"rank\": 0.12810646252444075, \"text\": \"Belgian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\"}, {\"begin\": 1257, \"end\": 1270, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Claire_Michel\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Claire Michel\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Claire_Michel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Claire_Michel\"}, {\"begin\": 1285, \"end\": 1290, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Switzerland\", \"score\": 0.9940236213544231, \"rank\": 0.006012032668016091, \"text\": \"Swiss\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Switzerland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Switzerland\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Belgian mediareported that\\u00a0Michel suffered from a four-day infection of E. coli and even had to go to hospital in Paris for treatment.\", \"from\": 1346, \"to\": 1480, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1346, \"end\": 1353, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\", \"score\": 0.8864394935273845, \"rank\": 0.12810646252444075, \"text\": \"Belgian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\"}, {\"begin\": 1460, \"end\": 1465, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999993488018, \"rank\": 6.51366676114574e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A statement from the Belgian Olympic Committee made the regretful announcement, noting \\\"Belgian Triathlon hope that lessons will be learned for future triathlon competitions.\\\"\", \"from\": 1482, \"to\": 1657, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1503, \"end\": 1528, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgian_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.403491311684803e-14, \"text\": \"Belgian Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgian_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgian_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 1570, \"end\": 1577, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\", \"score\": 0.8864394935273845, \"rank\": 0.12810646252444075, \"text\": \"Belgian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\"}, {\"begin\": 1578, \"end\": 1587, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Triathlon\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.716024399366333e-14, \"text\": \"Triathlon\", \"types\": [\"Q349\", \"Q1914636\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Triathlon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Triathlon\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The statement further expressed a desire to see \\\"circumstances that do not cause uncertainty among athletes, entourage and fans.\\\"\", \"from\": 1659, \"to\": 1788, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The announcement came after another\\u00a0Belgian triathlete\\u00a0Jolien Vermeylencommented\\\"While swimming under the bridge, I felt and saw things that we should not think about too much.\\\"\", \"from\": 1790, \"to\": 1967, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1826, \"end\": 1833, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\", \"score\": 0.8864394935273845, \"rank\": 0.12810646252444075, \"text\": \"Belgian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In addition,\\u00a0the Swiss Olympic Teamannounced the withdrawalof triathlete Adrien Briffod due to a stomach illness contracted after swimming in the river during earlier rounds.\", \"from\": 1969, \"to\": 2143, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2042, \"end\": 2048, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jeff_Adrien\", \"score\": 0.9999999899196155, \"rank\": 4.9148759784062316e-09, \"text\": \"Adrien\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jeff_Adrien\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jeff_Adrien\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Brifford was replaced by\\u00a0reserve Olympian\\u00a0Simon Westermann, but he also had to withdraw due to\\u00a0a\\u00a0gastrointestinal illness.\", \"from\": 2145, \"to\": 2267, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2178, \"end\": 2186, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"score\": 0.9999999888595995, \"rank\": 9.113739165318927e-09, \"text\": \"Olympian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\"}, {\"begin\": 2193, \"end\": 2203, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hans_Westermann\", \"score\": 0.9358040233693783, \"rank\": 0.06859651888551613, \"text\": \"Westermann\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hans_Westermann\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hans_Westermann\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Two dropouts within a few days are very unusual and, first and foremost, unfortunate for the athletes,\\\" the national team's press release read.\", \"from\": 2269, \"to\": 2413, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The mayor of Paris has denied that the river is polluted, calling the claim \\\"fake news.\\\"\", \"from\": 2415, \"to\": 2503, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2428, \"end\": 2433, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999993488018, \"rank\": 6.51366676114574e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The statement flies in the face of effortscosting in excess of $1.5 billionthat were made prior to the games to clean the river up, as well assubsequent testingof the water that found bacteria levels are below acceptable standards.\", \"from\": 2505, \"to\": 2736, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Swimming in the river has also been banned since 1923 due to the poor water quality and health hazards.\", \"from\": 2738, \"to\": 2841, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This latest development comes amid the furore in the women's boxing and the controversy of the ridiculous opening ceremony featuring drag queens and a man painted blue openly mocking Christianity.\", \"from\": 2843, \"to\": 3039, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3026, \"end\": 3038, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9992587687081919, \"rank\": 0.000721953295602129, \"text\": \"Christianity\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Your support is crucial in helping us defeat mass censorship.\", \"from\": 3041, \"to\": 3102, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Please consider donating viaLocalsor check out our uniquemerch.\", \"from\": 3103, \"to\": 3166, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Follow us on X@ModernityNews.\", \"from\": 3167, \"to\": 3196, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Now WHO would just crap in a RIVER?\", \"from\": 3198, \"to\": 3233, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Oh wait, they said it wasn't IN the RIVER - it was in the STREETS and then the RAIN flushed it into the RIVER!\", \"from\": 3235, \"to\": 3345, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Whew, for a moment there I thought people were just nasty and would crap in a RIVER!\", \"from\": 3347, \"to\": 3431, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"That happened to me once in the 90's at a waterpark in Montreal.\", \"from\": 3433, \"to\": 3497, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3488, \"end\": 3496, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montreal\", \"score\": 0.9999999998658495, \"rank\": 6.012994125073218e-11, \"text\": \"Montreal\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montreal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montreal\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Man-o-man I have never been that sick in my life for a week.\", \"from\": 3498, \"to\": 3558, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\":